1943;;Old Mother Riley Overseas;;British;;Oswald Mitchell;;Arthur Lucan, Kitty McShane;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Mother_Riley_Overseas;;Mother Riley is tricked out of her licence for a pub, and heads for Portugal to find her daughter who is working in the wine business. Along the way she is somehow mistaken for a famous pianist, but arrives in Portugal just in time to prevent her daughter from being kidnapped. She also manages to retrieve stolen port wine.[2][3]